ISO 9001, ISO-TS 16949, ISO 14001










Energy-efficient compressed air supply for turbo-charger test stands with “Waste-Heat-Recovery-System”EFRE funding for the enhancement of energy- and resource efficiencyBorgWarner Turbo Systems Engineering GmbH in Kirchheimbolanden received funding from the European Union´s European Regional Development Fund (EFRE).Aim of the funded project is the energy-efficient restructuring of the compressor units that are required for the compressed air supply of the exhaust turbocharger´s test stands in combination of a “Waste-Heat-Recovery-System” for the hot water generation.The energy savings will be achieved by the following actions:New automatic control-system for the compressor stations with high integrated energy data acquisition system for precise and fast responsive compressed air supply on demand.Replacement of the non-speed-controlled  by speed-controlled high efficient e-motors.Waste-Heat-Recovery-System integrated in compressor oil cooling circuit for hot water generation used for the heating of the buildings and washwater.
Open description of the funded program












