In Volatile Markets Do Analysts Think You Should Buy BorgWarner Inc. (NYSE:BWA)?


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Tuesday, 18 Jul 2017 06:55 AM  / 0 Comments




Following U.S. election volatility some analysts have updated their recommended target prices on shares of BorgWarner Inc. (NYSE:BWA).  	 According to the most recently released broker notes, 4 analysts have a rating of “strong buy” on the stock, 5 analysts “buy”, 10 analysts “neutral”, 2 analysts “sell” and 1 analysts “strong sell”. 	  



Latest Recommended Buy/Sell Side Ratings:
06/20/2017 – Guggenheim began new coverage on BorgWarner Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 45 price target on the stock.
06/16/2017 – BorgWarner Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Bank of America Merrill Lynch.  They now have a USD 27 price target on the stock.
06/08/2017 – BorgWarner Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Morgan Stanley.  They now have a USD 32 price target on the stock.
05/30/2017 – BorgWarner Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Deutsche Bank.  They now have a USD 54 price target on the stock.
05/01/2017 – BorgWarner Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at BMO Capital Markets.  They now have a USD 50 price target on the stock.
04/28/2017 – BorgWarner Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Jefferies.  They now have a USD 50 price target on the stock.
02/10/2017 – BorgWarner Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Barclays.  They now have a USD 39 price target on the stock.
01/04/2017 – BorgWarner Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Evercore ISI.  They now have a USD 42 price target on the stock.
12/19/2016 – BorgWarner Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Wells Fargo.  They now have a USD 42 price target on the stock.
12/13/2016 – BorgWarner Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Northcoast Research. 
11/22/2016 – Berenberg Bank began new coverage on BorgWarner Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 28 price target on the stock.
10/06/2016 – BorgWarner Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Goldman Sachs.  They now have a USD 35 price target on the stock.
09/06/2016 – BorgWarner Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Robert W. Baird.  They now have a USD 46 price target on the stock.
08/09/2016 – Seaport Global Securities began new coverage on BorgWarner Inc. giving the company a “” rating.
08/02/2016 – Buckingham Research began new coverage on BorgWarner Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 33 price target on the stock.
The share price of BorgWarner Inc. (NYSE:BWA) was down -0.09% during the last trading session, with a day high of 46.66. 1468885 shares were traded on BorgWarner Inc.’s last session. 
The stock’s 50 day moving average is 41.98 and its 200 day moving average is 41.14. The stock’s market capitalization is 9.81B. BorgWarner Inc. has a 52-week low of 31.21 and a 52-week high of 46.66.



BorgWarner Inc. is engaged in providing technology solutions for combustion, hybrid and electric vehicles. The Company’s segments include Engine and Drivetrain. The Engine segment’s products include turbochargers, timing devices and chains, emissions systems and thermal systems. The Engine segment develops and manufactures products for gasoline and diesel engines, and alternative powertrains. The Drivetrain segment’s products include transmission components and systems, all-wheel drive (AWD) torque transfer systems and rotating electrical devices. The Company’s products are manufactured and sold across the world, primarily to original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) of light vehicles (passenger cars, sport-utility vehicles (SUVs), vans and light trucks). The Company’s products are also sold to other OEMs of commercial vehicles (medium-duty trucks, heavy-duty trucks and buses) and off-highway vehicles (agricultural and construction machinery and marine applications.


