Search Links  
Product Search - Standard Version 















  
Engine Group
The Engine Group develops air management strategies and products to optimize engines for fuel efficiency, reduced emissions and enhanced performance. BorgWarner’s expertise in engine timing systems, boosting systems, ignition systems, air and noise management, cooling and controls is the foundation for this collaboration. 
 
Drivetrain Group
The Drivetrain Group harnesses a legacy of more than 100 years as an industry innovator in transmission and all-wheel drive technology. The group is leveraging its understanding of powertrain clutching technology to develop interactive control systems and strategies for all types of torque management. 
  


Key Technologies Morse Systems specializes in variable cam timing, chain driven engine timing systems and HY-VO® chains for FWD transmissions and transfer case applications.
Emissions Systems products focus on exhaust gas recirculation (EGR) systems, secondary air systems, advanced actuators, PTC cabin heaters, diesel cold-start and ignition technology for enhanced engine performance, fuel economy, and reduced emissions.
Thermal Systems specialize in thermal management including improved engine cooling while reducing emissions and fuel consumption.
Turbo Systems focus on turbochargers and boosting systems for passenger cars, light trucks and commercial vehicles. Systems enhance fuel efficiency, reduce emissions and enhance vehicle performance.
              
Key Technologies
Transmission Systems specialize in automated transmission clutch components and systems and offer complete electro-hydraulic control modules and components for a variety of transmission types.

PowerDrive Systems offers superior torque distribution and management systems, including a complete line of products for FWD-based AWD, RWD-based AWD, pure electric and hybrid applications. 

 
  













































