 comply with the demands customers have today and even those they will have tomorrow. In such a way the company rests assured that its products provide excellent quality, maximum power, unparalleled performance as well as long lasting service life.Since the company’s earliest days in 1899, the product assortment of BorgWarner has significantly expanded. The company carries a comprehensive line of new turbochargers, including the ones for Caterpillar engines, Cummins engines, Detroit Diesel engines, General Motors engines, and more. Among the products of the company are also rebuilt turbochargers for Detroit Diesel engines, Jonh Deere engines, Mercedes-Benz engines, etc. By offering product solutions that are perfectly tailored to customers’ specific needs, BorgWarner has grown to become a prosperous company that gained wide recognition.The company demonstrates its strong commitment to offering innovative technological solutions while considerably optimizing development processes. Since the company was formed when famous turbocharger manufacturers 3K and Schwitzer merged, BorgWarner has drawn upon a rich tradition of successes in turbocharging technology. Today BorgWarner continues to set new technical standards in this field. The company's up-to-date manufacturing technologies and approaches ensure that its products conform to strict quality specifications. The company offers a collection of BorgWarner, 3K and Schwitzer replacement turbochargers to aftermarket customers around the world.BorgWarner ReviewsAverage rating:	   4.8 - 5 reviews  /  Read All BorgWarner Reviews4.8 of 5Happy CustomerBorgWarner® - EFR Series EFR 7670 375-650 HP TurbochargerThis turbo is made for a fast races. Ideal for drag racers who want to make obscene power levels with reasonable spool. I had some problems installing it, but it all grades with power you have got. CARiD offers an unbeatable price, so i will return soon.DPosted by Derek (Hampden, NF) / October 11, 2015Was this review helpfu