Select VehicleSelect Year...Select Year... Make...Select Make...2Select Model...Select Model...3GOMy Garage:Vehicles Performance Parts / Replacement PartsReplacement Suspension Parts76,900 ProductsWithout a suspension system, you would not only have a bone shaking ride but little vehicle control as well. The tires would bounce in reaction to bumps, and tires that aren’t on the ground can’t direct, move or stop the vehicle. The suspension keeps the wheels in contact with the road surface for steering and traction, so power gets to the ground and you can remain in control. All suspensions have springs to absorb bumps and shock absorbers to control the action of the springs.Categories (24,539)Shocks & StrutsShock Absorbers, Strut Assemblies(6,489)Coil SpringsCoil Spring Sets, Coil Spring Seats(1,367)Leaf SpringsLeaf Spring Sets & Bushings(1,084)Air SuspensionAir Springs, Shocks, Air Lines(21,116)Control ArmsArm Assemblies, Strut Rods(12,621)Sway BarsSway Bar Bushings, End Links(4,672)Ball JointsUpper & Lower Ball Joints(95)Torsion BarsTorsion Bar Sets & Mounting Kits(323)Panhard BarsTrack Bars, Watts Links, Bushings(5,162)Shock & Strut HardwareUpper Strut Mounts, Shock Boots(372)Self-Leveling SensorsSelf Leveling Units & Relays(11,610)Suspension BushingsBushing Kits, Shaft Kits & Bumpers(1,056)Alignment KitsCamber Plates, Cam Bolts, Toe Kits(1,160)Suspension & Steering ToolsSpring Compressors, Axle Sockets(117)Suspension LubricantsGreasing Prevents WearFeatured BrandsMonroeArnottMOOGKYBDormanUnity AutomotiveMevotechFCSBilsteinGabrielACDelcoCentricSuncoreBeck ArnleyGenuineMiessler AutomotiveSachsSenSenFirst Equipment QualityURO PartsGSP North AmericaWestarOSC AutomotiveLemfoerderMotorcraftCardoneRight Stuff DetailingMoparOmix-AdaTRWThere are far too many suspension system designs for a detailed discussion here, but all can be divided into solid (beam) axle suspension and independent suspension. A solid axle is so called because the wheels on either side of the vehicle are linked by a rigid axle housing, and a bump in the road that affects one wheel will also disturb the wheel on the other side. Solid axles can be live axles that transmit power to the wheels or dead axles that do not. As the name implies, independent suspensions allow the wheels to move independently of each other, and the effect of a bump on the road encountered by one wheel will be isolated to that wheel and will not affect the wheel on the other side of the vehicle.Show items:6090120Sort by:RecommendedPrice Low to HighPrice High to LowTop Rated ProductsMonroe® Econo-Matic™ Complete Strut Assemblies(15 reviews)# sp4351Econo-Matic™ Complete Strut Assemblies by Monroe®. This ready-to-install complete strut assembly includes everything needed for strut replacement in an affordable, fully-assembled unit. You save time because spring compression is...Economical replacement alternative helping to ensure a complete repairHelps reduce installation time $56.05 - $134.91Bilstein® B4 Series Replacement Shocks and Struts(9 reviews)# sp4266B4 Series Replacement Shocks and Struts by Bilstein®. BILSTEIN has a legendary reputation for providing original equipment components to many of the world’s finest vehicle manufacturers.  The BILSTEIN B4 Series provides the same...Constant damping characteristics under any loadConsistent performance and handling give the vehicle a new car feel every time $28.68 - $634.07MOOG® Coil Spring Set(14 reviews)# sp5137Coil Spring Set by MOOG®. Upgrade your vehicle to MOOG coil springs that are designed to restore the original handling, reduce body sway and bring ride height to OE specifications. These coil springs ensure a seamless fit and...Direct fit, with no modificationsRestores and retains proper handling $25.07 - $179.45Arnott® Air Shocks and Struts(62 reviews)# sp16725Air Shocks and Struts by Arnott®. Designed to match the fine specifications and tolerances of OEM equipment. Available in 100% new or remanufactured form built with replacement